	title = {Language evolution to revolution: the leap from rich-vocabulary non-recursive communication system to recursive language 70,000 years ago was associated with acquisition of a novel component of imagination, called {Prefrontal} {Synthesis}, enabled by a mutation that slowed down the prefrontal cortex maturation simultaneously in two or more children – the {Romulus} and {Remus} hypothesis},
